inputs: Two roads diverged in a yellow wood,
outputs: And sorry I could not travel both

inputs: And be one traveler, long I stood
outputs: And looked down one as far as I could

inputs: To where it bent in the undergrowth;
outputs: Then took the other, as just as fair,

inputs: And having perhaps the better claim,
outputs: Because it was grassy and wanted wear;

inputs: Though as for that the passing there
outputs: Had worn them really about the same,

inputs: And both that morning equally lay
outputs: In leaves no step had trodden black.

inputs: Oh, I kept the first for another day!
outputs: Yet knowing how way leads on to way,

inputs: I doubted if I should ever come back.
outputs: I shall be telling this with a sigh

outputs: And that has made all the difference.
